{
  "texts": [
    "Samples with scores between τ s and the MZ threshold τ N are softly rejected by assigning them a smaller weight t s during training.",
    "This weighted penalty allows the model to remain cautious about uncertain cases without completely discarding them.",
    "By integrating both GMM-based and distribution-aware thresholds, our approach balances aggressive anomaly exclusion and the preservation of informative normal samples.",
    "AlgorithmIn the early stages of training, we train a model with a warm-up training phase that trains the model on instances with anomaly scores lower than the MZ threshold τ N for E epochs as the anomaly scores are randomly scattered.",
    "Next, we fit a GMM to the anomaly scores and set two thresholds, τ I and τ σ."
  ]
}